✅ Recommended `page.html.twig` snippet (place at top of `<body>`):
```twig
<a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focusable">
  {{ 'Skip to main content'|t }}
</a>
```

✅ CSS (in a `.css` file, not inline):
```css
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}

.sr-only.focusable:active,
.sr-only.focusable:focus {
  position: static;
  width: auto;
  height: auto;
  padding: 1rem;
  margin: 0;
  overflow: visible;
  clip: auto;
  white-space: normal;
  background: #000;
  color: #fff;
  z-index: 1000;
}
```

✅ Ensure `#main-content` exists in your layout:
```twig
<main id="main-content" role="main">
  {{ page.content }}
</main>
```

Do **not** put skip links via JavaScript or preprocess only — they must be static in the DOM for screen readers and keyboard users.

✅ Bonus: Use `drupal_add_locale()` if multilingual, and always wrap the anchor’s text with `t()` for translation.
